The paper discusses the perception of complexity in images, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses statistical analysis to understand the relationship between natural scene statistics and the perception of complexity, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the possible mediational role of natural frequencies in the perception of algorithmic complexity, which is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
